
[1]sip

   SIP, v.t.

   1. To take a fluid into the mouth in small quantities by the lips; as,
   to sip wine; to sip tea or coffee.

   2. To drink or imbibe in small quantities. Every herb that sips the
   dew.

   3. To draw into the mouth ; to extract; as, a bee sips nectar from the
   flowers.

   4. To drink out of. They skim the floods, and sip the purple flow'rs.
     __________________________________________________________________

